 academy, From History to Theory innovatively ties semantic shifts in academic discourse to key trends in American society, culture, and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDiscourse analysis. 0aHistoriographyxHistoryxUnited States. 0aHistoriographyxMethodologyxUnited States. 0aHistoriographyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aHistoriographyzUnited StatesxMethodology. 0aHistoryvTerminology. 0aHistoryxTerminology. 0aLinguistic changexHistoryxUnited States. 0aLinguistic changezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aReligionvTerminology. 0aReligionxTerminology. 0aSocial changexHistoryxUnited States. 0aSocial changezUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Historiography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948297423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520948297.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles